text: Tarcenay-Foucherans is a commune. It is in Bourgogne-Franche-Comté in the Doubs department in east France. The municipality was created on 1 January 2019 and consists of the former communes of Tarcenay (the seat) and Foucherans.Arrêté préfectoral 26 September 2018 == References == Category:2019 establishments in France Category:Communes in Doubs
title: Tarcenay-Foucherans
